This is an open-source, algorithm-agile HYBRID post-quantum cryptography
reference implementation on the finalized NIST standards ML-KEM (FIPS 203)
and ML-DSA (FIPS 204).

It depends on third-party open-source libraries (see requirements.txt /
pyproject.toml and the CycloneDX SBOM under sbom/), each under its own license.

VORLATH Shield is a REFERENCE IMPLEMENTATION. It is NOT FIPS 140-3 validated and
is NOT side-channel hardened. "CNSA 2.0" denotes the algorithm set, not a validated
module. Read SECURITY.md and THREAT_MODEL.md before any real use.
